          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Gamma spectra from the radiative capture of 3He",
                " particles by tritons have been obtained over the",
                " energy range 0.5 < E(He3) < 11.0 MeV.  Excitation",
                " curves and angular distributions are presented.",
                "The integrated cross section for the inverse reaction",
                " 6Li(gamma0,t)3He up to E(g) = 25 MeV is found to be",
                " 9.3 (1.4) MeV*mb.",
                "Strong transitions were seen to the ground and first",
                " two excited states of 6Li.",
                "Evidence is also found for a transition to the second",
                " t=1 state of 6Li the results are discussed in the",
                " framework of the direct-capture model. Substantial",
                " T+He-3 clustering is evident in the four observed 6Li",
                " final states."
              ]
            }
          ],
